description.p:
a controller, the controller comprising;



    

a controller processor, and

a controller memory storing processor-executable controller process steps,

wherein the controller processor is operative with the controller processor-executable process steps to:

i) receive the player identifier and the gaming data;

ii) receive product information concerning a plurality of products;

iii) determine, for each of the plurality of products, a respective approximate maximum price for which a product may be sold through a retail channel;

iv) determine a respective cost of each of the plurality of products;

v) determine a current value of each of the plurality of products based on a respective approximate maximum price and a respective cost;

vi) based on the gaming data, determine an expected profit resulting from an offer of each of the plurality of products; and

vii) determine to offer one of the plurality of products based on the current value of the one product and the expected profit resulting from an offer of the one product.

claim.claim-text:
1. A method of operating a gaming device including a plurality of instructions, the method comprising:
(a) causing an input device to enable a player to make an input corresponding to a wager for a play of a game;
(b) causing a processor to execute the plurality of instructions to determine an outcome for the play of the game;
(c) causing a display device to display the determined outcome;
(d) causing the display device to display to the player any monetary award associated with the displayed determined outcome, wherein the monetary award is based on the wager made by the player for the play of the game;
(e) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to identify a product which may be offered to the player, the identification based on gaming activity of the player;
(f) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to determine an approximate maximum retail price among a plurality of different prices for which the identified product may be sold through a retail channel;
(g) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to determine whether or not to offer the identified product to the player based on: (i) prior gaming activity of the player including a plurality of wagers made by the player, and (ii) the determined approximate maximum retail price; and
(h) if the determination is to offer the identified product to the player, causing the input device to enable the player to obtain the identified product in exchange for at least part of the monetary award associated with the displayed determined outcome.

11. A method of operating a gaming device including a plurality of instructions, the method comprising:
(a) causing an input device to enable a player to make an input corresponding to a wager for a play of a game;
(b) causing a processor to execute the plurality of instructions to determine an outcome for the play of the game;
(c) causing a display device to display the determined outcome;
(d) causing the display device to display to the player any monetary award associated with the displayed determined outcome, wherein the monetary award is based on the wager made by the player for the play of the game;
(e) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to receive player data corresponding to gaming activity of the player;
(f) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to determine an approximate maximum retail price among a plurality of different prices for which a product may be sold through a retail channel;
(g) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to offer the product to the player based on: (i) received player data corresponding to prior gaming activity of the player including a plurality of wagers made by the player, and (ii) the determined approximate maximum retail price; and
(h) causing the input device to enable the player to obtain the offered product in exchange for at least part of any monetary award displayed to the player.

32. A method of operating a gaming device including a plurality of instructions, the method comprising:
(a) causing an input device to enable a player to make an input corresponding to a wager for a play of a game;
(b) causing a processor to execute the plurality of instructions to determine an outcome for the play of the game;
(c) causing a display device to display the determined outcome;
(d) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to receive player data corresponding to gaming activity of the player;
(e) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to offer a product to the player based on: (i) received player data corresponding to prior gaming activity of the player including a plurality of wagers made by the player, and (ii) an approximate maximum retail price among a plurality of different prices for which the product may be sold through a retail channel;
(f) causing the display device to display to the player any monetary award associated with the displayed determined outcome, wherein the monetary award is based on the wager made by the player for the play of the game;
and
(g) enabling the player to accept the offered product.

34. A method of operating a gaming device including a plurality of instructions, the method comprising:
(a) causing an input device to enable a player to make an input corresponding to a wager for a play of a game;
(b) causing a processor to execute the plurality of instructions to determine an outcome for the play of the game;
(c) causing a display device to display the determined outcome;
(d) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to receive player data corresponding to gaming activity of the player, the gaming activity of the player including:
(1) data concerning interests of the player; and
(2) data concerning past activity of the player including a plurality of wagers made by the player;

(e) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to determine an approximate maximum retail price among a plurality of different prices for which a product may be sold through a retail channel, the determination based, at least in part, on:
(1) at least one past offer of the product;
(2) a cost of the product;
(3) a list price of the product;
(4) a demand for the product; and
(5) an availability of the product;

(f) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to detect a first request from the player to convert casino credit to currency;
(g) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to detect a second request from the player to discontinue a gaming session;
(h) causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to detect a first monetary award being displayed to the player, wherein the first monetary award is based on the wager made by the player for the play of the game;
(i) in response to the first and second requests being detected and the first monetary award being displayed to the player, causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to offer the player:
(1) the product to the player based on the received player data including data concerning past activity of the player including the plurality of wagers made by the player and on the approximate maximum retail price, and
(2) a second monetary award to the player, wherein the second monetary award is less than the first monetary award;

j) causing the input device to enable the player to make an input to accept the offer; and
(k) in response to receiving the input corresponding to the player accepting the offer, causing the processor to execute the plurality of instructions to cause the product and the second monetary award to be provided to the player in exchange for the first monetary award previously displayed to the player.
